rComments: Overall unpleasant experience. Critical thinking is bot encouraged, just memorize book definitions to get good grade. Stares at you the whole time u talk to her and cant give you an answer. Talks bad about colleagues which is very unprofessional.

Pretty good teacher, shares feedback on cases and is pretty clear on what expectations are. What's on the slides and the book is on the midterms and exams, no surprises. Quick to responding to emails to clarify things and makes sure to share announcements so students don't get lost.
An angel. I have no words. The best professor at Telfer.

My favourite professor, hands down. Extremely kind and conveys information in such a clear, concise way. Clearly loves what she does and takes her job seriously. Was really empathetic about the switching online situation- extremely responsive, understanding, and helpful. I wish she taught every class!!

If every professor was like Silvia, classes would be a dream. She is so passionate and clear in her lectures, and so caring/understanding. Her exams/midterms never have surprises, and she specifies which chapters to learn from the textbook. Cases are fine and good grade boosters. I feel so lucky to have had her as a prof! A true angel

This teacher is so nice and cares about her students. You need to be in class since she doesn't share her PP and a few parts are not mentioned in the book. Few cases to do in class in a group. Midterm and Final went well, I would take her again!
Her grading is way too tough and harsh. Doesn't upload on brightspace, and generally turns an easy course into a pain in the ass. Speaks like 6 languages tho which is cool I guess

Silvia is my FAVOURITE professor. Her lectures are mandatory because she doesn't post slides, but she explains concepts very well in class. Content is a little heavy post-midterm and is comprehensive, but as long as you pay attention in class and study a little everyday, you're golden. Love her, take her, you will love her too.

Professor Bonaccio is one of the best professors I've had at Telfer. She explains the content in a very well manner and uses great examples to help us retain information. She gives awesome midterm/final review sessions. She doesn't post her slides online, so make sure you go to class and do the textbook readings she asks you to do.

AWESOME PROF You can easily tell that she is very passioned about what she teaches in class Alwways smiling and encouraging She doesnt post any slides so you have to go to class, otherwise you would be so lost Her examples are funny and intersting

Silvia is honestly one of the most caring and friendly profs Ive had in Telfer. She has a very bubbly personality and makes the content of OB actually interesting. Never miss out on her midterm/ final review classes either! Attend class, ask questions, and its an easy A. Definitely recommend Prof Bonaccio!

Faced paced talking, often found I missed info. Midterm is MC and Short Answer where short answers needed critical, specific answers often said in her lectures, not in textbook. No presentation slides. Class average was a C for the only midterm. Final strictly multiple choice. Received a mere pass on final after studying. Cases 80-100%. I'd avoid.

Silvia is an amazing prof and truly cares about her work and students. She even makes an effort to learn names in a class of +100. Notes aren't online, so show up to the lectures. Material is kind of dry but she makes the best of it. Case studies are easy mark boosters and the midterm was easy (a lot of writing though). Final is all MCQ.

important to go to class as she dont post lectures and the exam includes things not in the textbook. you need to be very specific to get marks so its a good thing the exam is m/c. also answers questions well and very nice.
Made boring material somewhat interesting, probably one of the best profs at Telfer, highly recommend. Would give 7 chilies if I Ratemyprof allowed it.

The BEST adm teacher I've ever met!!! She teaches us something that is not included in the textbook but covered in the exams, but this is totally acceptable. Also the review class before exams really HELPS A LOT! She will list every basic knowledge point in bullets and provide us a really clear structure. Record the classes if u can!
Easy content, conveyed well. Willing to provide help outside class and is accommodating to students.
Lectures were the usual excitement, but necessary if you want to do well on the exams. Case studies were easy enough and done in groups. Similar to OB in terms of easiness.
HONESTLY, THERE ARE LITERALLY NO WORDS IN THE ENGLISH LANGUAGE THAT CAN DESCRIBE HOW ABSOLUTELY FANTASTIC SHE IS!!! :)

Awesome and best professor! One of my favourites in Telfer!  She cares about every student and course material. She will give acronyms, visuals, clear explanations of concepts which will help students! Cases and midterms are extremely easy as long as you review notes regularly. Also, I recommend you to attend every class and pay attention.

Overall, she is an awesome professor! Very friendly and best teacher for ADM2336! One of best profs of Telfer! She provides acronyms, visuals, point form notes and great explanations of concepts which will help you (helped me). Cases and midterms are easy as long as you study notes and attend class. Attend every class and review regularly=success!
Such a great Professor. She loves her students and really cares about the course material. She is also very clear in her expectations. Her exams cover the material perfectly!
Such an incredible prof. She is so sweet and genuine, and actually cares. Conveys the information very clearly. Make sure you actually attend classes. One of my favourite profs for sure!

Excellent prof. Very enthusiastic about course material. She explains concepts very clearly and provides lots of examples. She doesn't post lecture notes so you have to attend class. If you write down everything she says, you will do great on midterms and finals.
Great Prof! Interesting lectures and well explained content. Go to the exam reviews and you'll do fine. Not bad looking either.

The best professor I've had so far at Telfer. She's pretty and really takes her time to explain things to students. She's always ready to answer questions. Never changes grades on midterms or cases. Do well on the midterm and final and you'll do fine.
Clear lectures, challenging group case studies, very fair midterm and final exam

LOL AT HER EYES. She can be soo freaky. Sometimes I actually wondered what she was on. But very interesting lecturer, explains really well, gives tons of examples. I'm happy to have had her. Midterm was fair (study hard and focus on slides) final was tougher (watch the video!) and more textbook based. GOOD CLASS THOUGH! (HER EYES!)
One of the best profs at the Telfer school. She is really into what she teaches and is into the lectures. Very helpful, wants her students to do well. She's also very beautiful
Her eyes!!!

Great prof! Make sure you attend her classes because she does NOT post them online, but classes are very engaging. Cases are marked harder as the semester progresses, and the midterm short-answer questions are marked difficult as well.
just wow

Very nice prof. Group cases are straight from the textbook, as long as you pick a good group. MC MT&FE. Seems like a new prof, seriously enjoys the class still. Highly recommended.

Pick a good group at the beginning of the semester. The six cases are all fairly straight-forward but are marked very tightly. Midterm was fair however marks are given on a 0.125 basis. She is one of the most helpful professors at Telfer. She went over my case study with me and helped me identify problems areas and gave tips on how to improve for future case studies. Great attitude/genuine and sincere, unlike most business profs who seem like they don't care/don't really want to be there. You're a an excellent professor.

Pick a good group at the beginning of the semester.  The six cases are all fairly straight-forward but are marked very tightly. Not exactly interested in this course but she makes it interesting. She's one of the few profs who is not only genuinely interested in her topic but is able to get you somewhat interested too.
a reeealllyyy nice prof. very helpful. marks a bit hard. but midterm review was excellent! highly reccomended :D
you are the best Dr. Sylvia

Very keen and knowledgeable.  Eager to help students and ensure quality of learning.
Great!

Excellent prof. She really cares about her students. She always asks if her students have questions.  She'll explain and re-explain until her students understand.

This is an A course. Her exams are superduper easy! Just study her notes! Be prapared for the assignments ahead and know the material for them too.
